From: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Feb 2020 15:26:29 -0800
Subject: [1/3] KVM: nVMX: Don't emulate instructions in guest mode
Origin: https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux.git/commit?id=86dc39e580d8e3ffa42c8157d3e28249fd9a12c5
Bug-Debian-Security: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2020-2732

[ Upstream commit 07721feee46b4b248402133228235318199b05ec ]

vmx_check_intercept is not yet fully implemented. To avoid emulating
instructions disallowed by the L1 hypervisor, refuse to emulate
instructions by default.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
[Made commit, added commit msg - Oliver]
Signed-off-by: Oliver Upton <oupton@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx.c
@@ -11352,7 +11352,7 @@ static int vmx_check_intercept(struct kv
 	}
 
 	/* TODO: check more intercepts... */
-	return X86EMUL_CONTINUE;
+	return X86EMUL_UNHANDLEABLE;
 }
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_X86_64
